assetsRelativePathAndTextContent.b:
#!/bin/bash

set -e
source /etc/apache2/envvars
/usr/sbin/apache2ctl start

until [ -f /var/run/apache2/apache2.pid ]
do
	echo Waiting for /var/run/apache2/apache2.pid
	sleep 1
done

APP_PID=$(cat /var/run/apache2/apache2.pid)
while [ -e /proc/$APP_PID ]; do sleep 5; done

echo Apache service is down

<VirtualHost *>
    ServerName login.example.com
    ServerAlias login.example.com
    
    ErrorLog /var/log/apache2/login.example.com-error.log
    CustomLog /var/log/apache2/login.example.com-access.log combined
    
    RewriteEngine On
    RewriteRule /(.*) https://login.example.com/$1 [R,L]
</VirtualHost>

<VirtualHost *>
    ServerName ui.example.com
    ServerAlias ui.example.com
    
    ErrorLog /var/log/apache2/ui.example.com-error.log
    CustomLog /var/log/apache2/ui.example.com-access.log combined
    
    RewriteEngine On
    RewriteRule /(.*) https://ui.example.com/$1 [R,L]
</VirtualHost>

global
  user haproxy
  group haproxy
  tune.ssl.default-dh-param 1024

defaults
  timeout connect 5000
  timeout client 600000
  timeout server 600000

frontend port_4433
  mode http
  option forwardfor
  option http-server-close
  bind *:4433 ssl crt /certs
  reqadd X-Forwarded-Proto:\ https

  use_backend https_4433_login.example.com if { ssl_fc_sni login.example.com }
  use_backend https_4433_ui.example.com if { ssl_fc_sni ui.example.com }

frontend port_8080
  mode http
  option forwardfor
  option http-server-close
  bind *:8080
  reqadd X-Forwarded-Proto:\ http

  acl http_8080_login.example.com hdr(host) -i login.example.com
  acl http_8080_ui.example.com hdr(host) -i ui.example.com

  use_backend http_8080_login.example.com if http_8080_login.example.com
  use_backend http_8080_ui.example.com if http_8080_ui.example.com

backend https_4433_login.example.com
  option httpclose
  option forwardfor
  mode http
  server https_4433_login.example.com_1 127.0.0.1:10002 check

backend https_4433_ui.example.com
  option httpclose
  option forwardfor
  mode http
  server https_4433_ui.example.com_1 127.0.0.1:10003 check

backend http_8080_login.example.com
  option httpclose
  option forwardfor
  mode http
  server http_8080_login.example.com_1 127.0.0.1:10000 check

backend http_8080_ui.example.com
  option httpclose
  option forwardfor
  mode http
  server http_8080_ui.example.com_1 127.0.0.1:10001 check
